just another poem a lil long for me but if you have the time read n tell me what u think in my more recent indulging i begin to hear a whisper don't know from where another line another drink the whisper easily manipulated easily ignored for the moment the whisper i hear no more another line another drink afraid to lose my confidence maybe it's already gone i can't even remember me it's been so long another line another drink as the whispers get louder i start to see all this destruction continuously following me another line another drink not the alcohol not the drug just bad luck ya thats it my life does suck another line another drink whispers get louder as i spiral out of control before the tornado hits i need to save my soul another line another drink how much have i forgotten how much time have i wasted how many sleepless nights how much unused talent not tasted do you think its too long should i have stopped sooner or do you think it's ok very insperational moving great poem i like it Jim Morrison Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Social rule The Marshall Mathers LP One Tree Hill (TV series) The Human Stain The Shining (film) Jon Secada Alcoholic beverage I'm Sorry I Haven't a Clue 50 Cent Shaggy dog story Delta Goodrem Night (book) Avenue Q Mothers Against Drunk Driving Alcoholism Marie Antoinette Tenali Ramakrishna Manic Street Preachers Steven Wright Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Hansel und Gretel Traumatic incident reduction Mindy McCready Episodes of Lost (Season 2) John Farnham Journey (band) Dead Like Me Pitaten Bong Michael Garibaldi Zagreus (Doctor Who audio) Futurama (TV series - season 5) Vampire Futurama (TV series - season 2) Hearing impairment Freddy Fender Brian Jones (musician) The Smoking Room Timeline of heavy metal The Amber Spyglass Good Morning, Vietnam Sin City Angelus (Buffy the Vampire Slayer) Insomnia Ravenloft domains The Raven Carrie Jacobs-Bond Straight edge Muslim ibn Aqeel The Death Gate Cycle The Doors Charles Bukowski Billboa